cs.DC, cs.NI, cs.OS, cs.Distributed, cs.AR 

This paper is primarily focused on improving the performance of remote procedure calls (RPCs) in datacenter networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the use of lossy Ethernet and lossless fabrics, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of a state machine replication system, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.OS (Operating Systems). The paper also discusses the use of specialized distributed systems, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.Distributed (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the use of programmable switches and FPGAs, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
